> Is there anything better than a big bowl of mac and cheese? Yes: one you don’t have to painstakingly make from scratch! This cheesy mac is ready when you are, quick to heat up, and (most importantly) extremely delicious—perfect for serving alongside your BBQ feast.

> Keep frozen or refrigerated until ready to eat.

RECOMMENDED: Bring a #pot{} of water to a boil. Place @White Cheddar Mac & Cheese{1%30oz package} in pot; cook for ~{20%minutes}, then carefully remove. (Caution: Bag will be very hot.) Cut one corner with #scissors{} and pour into #serving bowl{}.

ALTERNATIVELY: Cut one corner of the bag; pour mac and cheese into a #microwave-safe container{}. (Do not microwave in cup.) Cover loosely with #microwave-safe plastic wrap{} or a #paper towel{}. Microwave on high, stirring halfway through, ~{5-6%minutes}. (Caution: Container and mac and cheese will be very hot.)